@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home Page";
}

<div class="text-center">
    <h2 class="display-4">Welcome to VioRentals</h2>
    <h4>
        The application aims to address the issue of managing and organizing a significant amount of data on a computer by providing tools for monitoring customer activity, 
        tracking movie availability, and more. Additionally, it offers various functionabilities such as CRUD operations for movies and customers, search bar, advanced pagination,
        the ability to rent movies and security for accessing administration features. With this application, you can effectively store and manage large amounts of information on your computer.
    </h4>
</div>
<br />
<h3>Application features:</h3>
<ul class ="list-group">
    <li>CRUD operations for movies and customers</li>
    <li>Search bar for movies and customers</li>
    <li>Advanced pagination</li>
    <li>Ability to change the displayed amount of records from 10 to 100</li>
    <li>Ability to jump to any page, not just moving by 1</li>
    <li>Ability to rent a movie to any user (1 the same movie can be rented and max 5 movies at the same time)</li>
    <li>Security to access the administration features</li>
    <li>Login and register</li>
    <li>Api for customers and movies</li>
    <li>DTO- Data Transfer Objects for movies and customers</li>
    <li>Bootstrap template</li>
</ul>
<br />
<h3>Extensions:</h3>
<ul class="list-group">
    <li>AutoMapper</li>
    <li>Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore extensions</li>
    <li>Jquery</li>
    <li>SwashBuckle - Swagger</li>
</ul>
